extend ../../layouts/nested-2
block main
	h2.flex-title type()
	p
		| The <code>type()</code> method maps directly to
		| <a href="http://webdriver.io/api/action/setValue.html">setValue() method</a> on WebdriverIO. This method
		| sends a sequence of keystrokes to an element (it clears the value beforehand).
	.element-area
		input(type="text", id="text1")
		pre.language-markup.line-numbers
			code
				| &lt;input type="text" id="text1" /&gt;
	pre.language-javascript.line-numbers
		code
			| 'use strict';
			| <br>
			| var drive = require('datadriver');
			| <br>
			| drive.execute({
			|   "execute": {
			|     "action": "redirect",
			|     "page": "api/execute/type.html"
			|   }
			| });
			| <br>
			| drive.execute({
			|   "selector": "#text1",
			|   "execute": {
			|     "action": "type",
			|     "text": "hello, world"
			|   }
			| });
	p And this is our expected output:
	pre.language-bash.line-numbers
		code
			| $ grunt webdriver:execute --url=http://datadriver.io
			| Running "webdriver:execute" (webdriver) task
			| <br>
			| ⚙ redirecting to "http://datadriver.io/api/execute/setViewportSize.html"
			| ⚙ executing "setValue" on "#text1".
			| 0 passing